	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104772736070349><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104772736070349>RE: what is the best pet</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104772736070349#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=181619><span id= >animekenji</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>279 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Mar 15th 6:56 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>These are my personal observations based on my limited experience with mage pets. They may have other strengths/weaknesses I haven't seen yet, but here's what I have seen.<br><br>Water pets are probably the best all around pets. They are fairly balanced in terms of hp and damage output. They aren't the best in any one area, but they aren't the worst either. They also have a higher regen rate than other pets so you won't be casting renew elements as often during downtime. Water pets also seem to suck up poison based attacks like they were candy. Air pets don't hit very hard (at least mine didn't which was I stopped using it), but are good at avoiding being hit. Earth pets have high hit points but damage is only average. Earth pets also seem to need the most healing after a fight because they don't dodge well. They can also root. Fire pets have the best damage output and can cast DD fire spells, but have lower hp. I would keep a water pet with me most of the time unless I was battling mobs where the specific abilities of another type would be more helpful.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Mar 15 06:24:02 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>If you were me and I were you, would we still be friends?</td></tr>
