	   <a name=104788593480432></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104788593480432><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104788593480432>RE: The Epic Pet</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104788593480432#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93315><span id=Scholar>Jeroo</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>49 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 17th 3:00 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>From 50-61 the epic pet is godly.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing comes close to it.  Trust me on this.<br><br>A buffed, armored, and weaponed 61 air is about equal to the epic pet for tanking ability.  It's still not as high for damage output.<br><br>For fighting mobs up to level 62 (mob's level, not yours), use the epic.  It's damage output is more than any other pet.  For level 62 mobs and higher, use the appropriate 61+ pet.  The higher level of the pop pets allow them to land their spells on the mobs, whereas the epic can't land its proc on anything level 62 or higher.<br>&nbsp;<br>--<br>Jeroo Ashstaff</td></tr>
