<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=104743249847259></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104743249847259><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104743249847259>Levels 12-55 solo or partnered</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104743249847259#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=184766><span id=Sage>jmspiers</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>16 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 11th 9:02 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey all,<br><br>I've been scanning these message boards and have been seeing a lot of the &quot;where do I go next?&quot; question. I decided to put together a few notes on suggested places to go either solo (preferably with KEI) or with a partner. This is not meant to be an all inclusive guide of course, just a few suggestions.<br><br>A couple of notes though before I give the break down on places to go. First of all, from 12-55 you shouldn't have to group at all unless you have a bad connection, or are just bored. However it's never a bad idea to group occasionally every few levels so you stay up to date with your group tactics, ESPECIALLY if your mage is your first real character. Also, I recommend going everywhere with KEI, it's definitely worth the money (playing solo you'll make more than enough to cover the donation cost), but unfortunately KEI is supposedly being limited to players 41 and above soon *sigh*. Oh well, I did up to 35 with no KEI so I know it can be done =).<br><br>With that said, here is the break down of places that I suggest.<br><br>Levels 12-14: The 3 sirens on the spires in OOT. Just ride the boat from freeport to BB, you'll pass in between the spires. Jump off and when you need to leave gate out. The sirens will not help each other, and they spawn every 6 minutes.<br><br>Levels 14-16: Estate of Unrest, watch for trains.<br><br>Levels 16-24: Lake of Ill Omen. Work your way around the lake, the mobs get higher as you go.<br>OR<br>Levels 16-24: Paludal Caverns either partnered or in a full group (I really recommend this route since it will give you a great chance to learn group tactics). NOTE: You can stay here till 26 easily, some stay till 27.<br><br>Levels 24-30: Highhold Keep, killing goblins. In a group if you like, or if the lookout room is open you can solo that. If you are evil or just don't care about Qeynos, EFP, and WFP faction then you can kill the guards till 34+. You can also camp the spires around the entrance to splitpaw in South Karana, or you can solo in the bedroom in Splitpaw, or group in the main room.<br><br>Levels 30-34: Guards in Highhold if you're evil or don't care about faction, South Karana and Splitpaw if you're good.<br><br>A SPECIAL NOTE AT THIS POINT! =): Lots of people go to Dawnshroud Peaks at this level. I'm not knocking it if that's what you did, but it's not even half the exp of the place that I'm about to show you, I promise. I did levels 35-52 in 6 days if that's any indicator of how good the exp is.<br><br>Levels 34-39: One place, and one place only to be (ok two places). 1) Eastern Wastes, ask for the loc of the U-Tree when you get into the zone, everyone will know what you're talking about, kill Ulthorks and Walruses. 2) Burning woods. Read up on some specific strategies for the zone on this site and find some good spots. I did EW so I can't tell you how good BW is, but it's supposed to be comparable. Also there are many different places to camp there and it can take you to level 50 easily. If you do the EW route save the ulthork tusks, they sell for 40pp to players and are pretty common.<br><br>Levels 39-44: Dreadlands in the yeti cave in the NW corner. A very little know camp spot. They are aggro but their aggro range is so small you can walk right past them and fight them in place next to their buddies without getting adds. There are 7 that spawn in there, with an 18 minute timer. Very occasionally there is an 8th that will walk through the hall so keep an eye out. At 45 you can move down to DL proper. There are 2 sets of ruins north of the KC entrance. If you camp on the north side of either set of those ruins you will not get any roamers, and you can pull singles to there solo.<br><br>Levels 45-51: Echo caverns, the non-hidden side, camp the bugs and fiends until level 49, then at 49 the bugs and fiends are still good but you can do the Taskmaster's room also. If a mob named Xilniov spawns STAY OUT OF THE ROOM! =). He's a royal pain in a place where the sun don't shine, but he'll despawn after about 15 minutes or so. An alternative to Echo Caverns if it is camped fully is Burning Woods, again, read some strategy guides on places to camp (hint: the hornet's nest, but there are many others). A 3rd alternative from 48 on is the next strategy . . .<br><br>Levels 51-55: Bards and nobles on the 2nd floor of Highhold Keep. This will ruin your faction in Qeynos, Antonica Bards, EFP, and WFP (although it improves Ring of Scale and some other ones) so if you care about your faction in those cities then I wouldn't do that route. You can also solo in PoJ although it's very dangerous (the mobs will assist each other until you are 56). You can get a partner or 2 though and easily own PoJ. There are too many strategies for taking PoJ to list here, but just don't pull the sentries until they get the pathing problems fixed, and when you are fighting in the halls make sure you stay up against them or mobs in the cells will add in, the same goes if you are pulling a mob back to the zone out - stay on the wall when you pull it to avoid adds from the cells. <br><br>There is Neriak 3rd gate also (which I haven't personally tried), uhmmmm gnolls in Jaggedpine (if the nec or SK ones poison you when you're under about 60pct health gate out RIGHT AWAY and get a heal), and uhmmmmm oh yes Seafury Cyclopses in OOT (You can actually start there around 44 or 45 but I would recommend the other places I listed first).<br><br>One more alternative for about 49-52 is Wyverns and drakes in Cobalt Scar (you have to get a GG or TL in but it's worth it). The drakes drop a 500 damage AE so when you pull them get your pet in there then get out of range and hit them with a long range bolt. If you have decent resists and wear a shard of the core, elemental blanket, and elemental shield yourself then you'll often resist it anyway.<br><br>I hope all of these notes help someone. Good luck fellow mages!<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Mar 11 20:32:59 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Baron Reeshan Ragefire, Magus of the 56th Flame, Drinal<br>Mathurin Kerbouchard, Bard of the 36th Song, Drinal<br>Lenrok Thunderwolf, Warrior of the 37th Circle, Drinal</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
