	   <a name=104646566183774></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104646566183774><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104646566183774>RE: Pet Armor ??</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104646566183774#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73372><span id=Sage>Malaclypse</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>131 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Feb 28th 4:27 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, you raise some excellent questions. First off yes your pets do gain benefits from summoned armor. This has been confirmed. At the mages tower (<a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower" target=_new>http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower</a>) there has been some extensive discussion on this topic and thanks much to Nemuneir Noldaron from ARo for doing the research.<br><br>Basically yeah, ac items increase your pets AC making them get hit less hard. They also benifit from stat items and resist gear. This would be backed up by the 61+ pet summoned items which have massive stat bonuses.<br><br>Also items with effects will work with pets. For instance, an earth pet with gnoll hide whips will proc them and stun a mob. And 5 mages with air pets and gnoll hide whips can drop pretty damn much anything under 55 in like 30 seconds... mmm... mage group.... /drool...<br><br>sorry, got sidetracked. Anyway, basically your pet will equip, use, and benifit from pretty much any item you give them, also ignoring the lore tag. However they will not use no drop items. As to the focus items....<br><br>Well from what I've heard and experienced they DO get the hp bonuses from them. The catch is, most pets (with the exception of the 50+ fire pets) don't have an actual mana pool. Their nukes are classified under skills as opposed to spells. This has been confirmed by mage/enc duels and attempted mana drain on pets.<br><br>So at a guess I'd say no. However, the 50+ fire pet DOES have a mana pool, confirmed in the same manner, I've also heard that these pets buffed with mana regen cast more frequently. The foci MIGHT work with those. Not sure if it's ever been parsed tho. However considering that pets use other worn effects such as haste, I'd think it would be likely that they would use the foci effects as well, which would hopefully make the fire pets suck less.<br><br>Soon as I ding 58 and grab the gvoc fire I'll parse it and post. It's a very interesting question, and I hope I was able to answer it in part.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar, 57th season vending machine, Leader of Defiant Heroes and arch nemesis of the evil squirrel empire[tm].<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Feb 28 15:55:13 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
